I"²<p>Screen command on Linux is a useful utility for those people who work on multiple screen using SSH session. This command allows you to open multiple session in a terminal even if you are not in a graphical session. This also allows you to share a session with other users or to attach and detach to a remote terminal session. Screen command is used when you need to perform a long-running task on a remote machine.</p>
